author: Georgi Kantchev
title: Fall in U.S. Oil Stockpiles Helps Push Prices Up a Tad
text:
LONDON—Oil prices rose modestly on Wednesday as Chinese stock markets rallied and an industry group reported a drop in U.S. oil stockpiles.
The Shanghai Composite Index closed 1.2% higher after falling as much as 5% earlier in a volatile session. A surprise devaluation of the yuan earlier in the month sparked fears about the economic health of the world’s second biggest oil consumer at a time when the market remains heavily...
